Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 84a (FBgn0037501) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a (Grosjean et al., 2011; Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4 (Benton et al., 2009). The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 29.5 in females and 24 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: This neuron was indirectly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single coeloconic sensillum (Grosjean et al., 2011).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 31a (FBgn0051718) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 posterior compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 posterior compartment (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1 (Benton et al., 2009). There are approximately 15 of these per antenna (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Nava Gonzales et al. (2021) - FBrf0250923 unsure whether this is ac1C or ac1D.

label.value: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac1

value.value: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1 (Silbering et al., 2011). It responds strongly to changes in humidity (Yao et al., 2005). The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 15 in females and 16 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Nava Gonzales et al. (2021) - FBrf0250923 unsure whether this is ac1C or ac1D.

value.value: Adult olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 92a (FBgn0038789) and the co-receptors Ir25a (FBgn0031634) and Ir76b (FBgn0036937). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM1 compartment (Silbering et al., 2011; Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1 (Benton et al., 2009) and it responds to ammonia (Min et al., 2013). There are approximately 15 of these cells in females and 16 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

Adult olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75a (FBgn0036757) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral DP1l glomerulus and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral DP1l (Silbering et al., 2011; Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2 (Benton et al., 2009). The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 15 in females and 12 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: This neuron was indirectly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single coeloconic sensillum (Benton et al., 2009).

label.value: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac2

value.value: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2 (Silbering et al., 2011).

definition.value: This neuron was indirectly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single coeloconic sensillum (Benton et al., 2009). This ORN responds strongly to changes in humidity (Yao et al., 2005).

value.value: Adult olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 41a (FBgn0040849) and the co-receptors 25a (FBgn0031634) and 76b (FBgn0036937). It innervates antennal lobe glomerulus VC5 (Schlegel et al., 2021) bilaterally (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2 (Benton et al., 2009). There are approximately 15 of these cells in females and 12 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor 75b and the co-receptor Ir8a (Silbering et al., 2011; Prieto-Godino et al., 2017). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac3 type I and its axonal terminals are found in glomerulus DL2d (Prieto-Godino et al., 2017). It has a stronger response to butyric acid and a weaker response to propionic acid, compared to Ir75c neurons (Prieto-Godino et al., 2017). There are approximately 8 of these cells per antenna (Schlegel et al., 2021).

definition.value: This neuron was directly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single neuron (Benton et al., 2009). Prieto-Godino et al. (2017) showed that these cells do not express Ir15a and previous detection of Ir75a (Benton et al., 2009) was likely due to transcription of the 5' end of Ir75a at the 3' end of Ir75b transcripts, rather than genuine Ir75a coding transcripts. They also show that cells expressing the Ir75b and Ir75c proteins are distinct (with previous co-occurrence similarly due to transcriptional run off from Ir75c).

label.value: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac4

value.value: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptors (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4 (Silbering et al., 2011).

definition.value: This neuron was indirectly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single coeloconic sensillum (Benton et al., 2009).

value.value: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptor (Ir) 76a (FBgn0260874) and the co-receptors Ir76b (FBgn0036937) and Ir25a (FBgn0031634). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM4 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4 (Benton et al., 2009). There are approximately 30 of these cells in females and 24 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: This neuron was indirectly shown to be olfactory by electrophysiological recordings of a single coeloconic sensillum (Benton et al., 2009).

value.value: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptor (Ir) 64a (FBgn0035604) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating an ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the corresponding contralateral glomerulus. There are approximately 16 of these cells on each side and they can be split into two subtypes, one that innervates the DC4 glomerulus and one that innervates DP1m (Ai et al., 2010). Its dendrite transduces signals from the grooved sensillum of chamber III of the sacculus (Shanbhag et al., 1995).
Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that houses the dendrites of olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs) Ir75a, Ir41a and Ir75d (Grabe et al., 2016).

Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that is innervated by two olfactory receptor neurons (ORN), one expressing Or35a and the other expressing either Ir75b or Ir75c (Prieto-Godino et al., 2017). These sensilla are present on the posterior antennal surface (Benton et al., 2009).

Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that houses the dendrites of olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs) Ir84a, Ir76a and Ir75d (Benton et al., 2009; Grabe et al., 2016).There are more of these sensilla in females than males (Grabe et al, 2016).
Ventral-most chamber of the sacculus of the antenna, where the opening is located (Shanbhag et al., 1995).
Middle chamber of the sacculus of the antenna. It has several compartments, each containing a single sensillum (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

Dorsal-most and largest chamber of the sacculus of the antenna. It has a ventral and a dorsal compartment, which differ in the type of sensilla they contain. The compartments are separated by a thick cuticular flap that extends lateromedially (Shanbhag et al., 1995).
Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some sacculus (FBbt:00004179).
VM7 glomerulus dorsal to VM7v.

Adult antennal lobe glomerulus found dorsal to glomerulus V and ventral to VC5 (Task et al., 2022). It can be subdivided into three (lateral, medial and ventral) compartments based on the axonal terminals of sensory neurons, but no divisions can be made based on projection neuron dendrite distribution (Task et al., 2022; Schlegel et al., 2021). It receives input from ammonia-responsive neurons (Vulpe et al., 2021).

definition.value: VC5 glomerulus renamed to VM6 based on Schlegel et al. (2021), current VC5 glomerulus (FBbt:00007104) was previously known as VC3m. Bates et al. (2020) and Marin et al. (2020) refer to VM6 as VC5 (Schlegel et al., 2021).

value.value: Neuron that expresses tachykinin (FBgn0037976).
Neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418).

Cell of the embryonic/larval midgut that expresses tachykinin (FBgn0037976). In the late third instar, tachykinin expressing cells in the midgut are located posteriorly, just anterior to the attachment of the Malpighian tubules and have a morphology consistent with an endocrine role.

definition.value: Siviter et al., 2000, observed tachykinin expressing cells in the midgut at embryonic stage 17 and in late third instar larvae using an antibody raised against locust tachykinin.
